==English==

===Etymology===
From French [[quart]], from Latin [[quartus]], '''one-fourth'''.

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɔː(r)t|-ɔː(r)t]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#A unit of liquid [[capacity]] equal to two [[pint]]s; one-fourth (quarter) of a gallon. Equivalent to 1.136 liters in the UK and 0.946 liter (liquid quart) or 1.101 liters (dry quart) in the U.S.

